	<!-- message -->
	<p>/salute<br />
<br />
I'm sure the moderators will move this to the appropriate forum very soon, just wanted to post it here to get the most exposure because it really helped me. Wanted the chance to reach the most poeple...<br />
<br />
I've had problems in the past going link dead, often in the Bazaar, and found this little trick that seems to prevent it. At times, you can do a /who command to save yourself from going link dead, but this trick seems to take care of all that for you.<br />
<br />
After you enter the game, go into windowed mode and open a command prompt window. Basically you are going to Ping your own internal address, which seems to keep your network connection alive in certain of these link death situations.<br />
<br />
Your internal address is 127.0.0.1, and the ping command has a -t switch to continually run the ping. You can also use the -L switch to set the size of the packet, to keep it small.<br />
<br />
So, the command I use at the command prompt is:<br />
<br />
ping -t -L 8 127.0.0.1<br />
<br />
<img src="http://www.eqguild.net/guilds/empire/images/ping1.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
While running behind your EQ, the window looks like this. I hope this helps some of you out there, it seems like it's been working pretty well for me.<br />
<br />
<img src="http://www.eqguild.net/guilds/empire/images/ping2.gif" border="0" alt=""></p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Thual<br />
Troll Prophet</div>
	
