	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I don't think non-EQ network activity has anything to do with you getting booted to desktop. I have left myself in the bazaar many many times over night with no issues, but then there are some times when the server goes down or the bazaar zone crashes (which seems to happen quite often) and I end up at desktop or in crash-land.<br />
Even if non-EQ network activity does make a difference, a ping to your local loopback address (127.0.0.1) will have no effect whatsoever since your packets will never leave your network stack and won't generate any network packets. At least ping some host that is really out there somewhere.<br />
<br />
Nipper Ripper<br />
64 Troll Shaman<br />
Order of Draconis<br />
Xev</p>
	
	
	
	
	
