	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Thats a pretty nice trick for not going LD. <br />
<br />
Here is another for Windows XP users. XP has a known fault in the power management service. When your computer hybernates it turns off power to your network card, but when it comes back up it has trouble re-initializing the network card. So.... Turn off your hibernation Feature!<br />
<br />
I have been staying on all night (barring updates) with this trick.<br />
<br />
It also works if ou keep loosing connection to your DSL/CABLE connection.</p>
	
	
	
