	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /> There are several game bugs running around that become really significant due to the number of people in the bazaar, and the ability of certain spells to knock people offline.<br />
When setting up your trader for the night, do the following:<br />
Minimize clip plane, set opacity to 0%, /showspelleffects off<br />
face a wall or look at the floor<br />
turn off all chat - ooc, shout, auction, guild, all chat channels<br />
set all spells to yourself or group<br />
make sure badword filter is off (/filter badword)<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Thanks for these ideas.  I tried several of them on my vendor last night.  And for the first time he stayed logged in all night.  I left him up today and if he’s still up when I get home I’ll consider it a success.  I always have my clip plane turned all the way down, as it’s far easier to maneuver in the bazaar that way.  But I also turn off all chat, turned off spell effects and turned off spells.<br />
<br />
I’ve not logged in any other characters yet, but from past experience I’m assuming these changes are universal.  Is there any way to make these changes affect ONLY my vendor?</p>
	
	
	
