<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Svigermor</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Apr 2003<br />
	Location: Los Angeles
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Got a tip from guildmates that works very nice for me.  Seems to be some bugs in the link code so leave all channels, turn off ooc,shout,auction, guildchat etc.<br />
<br />
After applying this my vendor bot has been dead stable in Bazaar apart from those times when the zone is actually going down - cant do much about those.<br />
<br />
Another practical thing is just go to the back away from the crowd.  People wanting to buy anything from you dont browse trough traders anyway and its just as easy to find your skinny mule in the back using the compass-feature in /bazaar as it is trying to sort trough a crowd that looks like someone just shouted 'MGB HoV'.<br />
<br />
-- <br />
Svigermor, Ogre shaman<br />
Mithaniel Marr server</p>
	
	
	
	
	
