	<!-- message -->
	<p>uhm.. not to sound rude but what the original Poster posted wont help in anyway with going Linkdead..<br />
<br />
The reason people were going Link Dead every couple mins was due to a Routing Problem inbetween Your internet provider and Sonys Bandwidth provider, to see if there is a problem click START > RUN > command > tracert servername.everquest.com i.e. druzzilro.everquest.com   if you see anything over 250ms OR if you see -> * <-- those alot thats where your problem is just a bad routing problem..<br />
<br />
there are a few things you can do to make it so your internet connection is better.. you do have to have some Knowledge of how windows and networking works. there are Some programs out there that do all the work for ya personally i cant list any off cuz i dont use em <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" />..  <br />
<br />
might check online for something that Optimizes Internet connections <br />
<a href="http://www.speedguide.net/" target="_blank">http://www.speedguide.net/</a> <-- great info / downloads to optimize yer computer for use with the internet <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
<br />
oh and ping -t 127.0.0.1 just pings yer computer you could be offline and do that and it wont make any difference..<br />
<br />
just like if you had a network card and its ip# was  192.168.0.1.. and if yer on cable and yer ip was 24.76.243.2 and u pinged it all u would be doing was clogging up yer own internet connection and litterly wont keep you on a server thats trying to send you information and that information is getting lossed some where between the server and you.</p>
	
	
	
	
