	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />uhm.. not to sound rude but what the original Poster posted wont help in anyway with going Linkdead..<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Hmm, you can of course choose to think whatever you like.<br />
<br />
I know, for a fact, that I went Linkdead over 30 days in a row. I began to ping my internal loop address and the LD stopped.<br />
<br />
<br />
Last night, I did not run the loop to again test the theory. Link Dead.<br />
<br />
So, for me this solution is working very, very well.<br />
<br />
It is my opinion that the Linkdeath that I am having has nothing to do with any traffic, but somehow my Router is getting bombed with tons of packets and just stops responding.<br />
<br />
Again, I never suggested that this would work for you, him, or anyone else but please refrain from making such general statements. It HAS worked for me, and a few people I know.<br />
<br />
